<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1292,1424]" pageId="33" pageNumber="270">
Distributed throughout the north-east shelf of Sakhalin Island (
<bibRefCitation author="Budnikova" box="[851,1209,1292,1317]" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" refString="Budnikova, L. L. &amp; Bezrukov, R. G. (2003) Composition and distribution of amphipods (Amphipoda, Gammaridea, Caprellidea) on the shelf and upper slope of eastern Sakhalin Island. Izvestiya TINRO, 135, 197 - 220. [in Russian with English summary]" type="journal article" year="2003">
Budnikova and Bezrukov, 
<number box="[1150,1209,1292,1316]" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dzhurinskyi" box="[1220,1431,1292,1317]" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" refString="Dzhurinskyi, V. L. (2013) Suborder Gammaridea. In: Sirenko, B. I. (Eds), Check-list of species of free-living invertebrates of the Russian Far Eastern seas. Explorations of the fauna of the seas, 75 (83), St. Petersburg, pp. 123 - 138." type="journal article" year="2013">
Dzhurinskyi, 
<number box="[1372,1431,1292,1316]" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; our data) (
<figureCitation box="[269,355,1327,1352]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1249,1271]" captionTargetBox="[459,1127,193,1222]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[459,1128,193,1228]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 24. Distribution of Melitoides species on the shelf of Sakhalin Island and nearest area." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251738/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="270">
Fig. 
<number box="[323,355,1328,1352]" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Also known from Bering Sea and Arctic Ocean, where widely distributed across the Siberian Arctic. 
<taxonomicName box="[235,377,1364,1388]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melitoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makarovi">
<emphasis box="[235,377,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="270">M. makarovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found between 
<quantity box="[606,719,1364,1388]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" unit="m" value="125.0" valueMax="230.0" valueMin="20.0">20–230 m</quantity>
on the sand bottom. Inside the Sakhalin shelf occurs in depth of 
<quantity box="[151,264,1400,1424]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.32" metricValueMin="0.88" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" unit="m" value="160.0" valueMax="232.0" valueMin="88.0">88–232 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Budnikova" box="[278,745,1399,1424]" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" refString="Budnikova, L. L. &amp; Bezrukov, R. G. (2003) Composition and distribution of amphipods (Amphipoda, Gammaridea, Caprellidea) on the shelf and upper slope of eastern Sakhalin Island. Izvestiya TINRO, 135, 197 - 220. [in Russian with English summary]" type="journal article" year="2003">
Budnikova and Bezrukov, 
<number box="[578,637,1400,1424]" pageId="33" pageNumber="270" value="2003.0">2003</number>
; our data
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
